{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1373,"text":"Most of us think of motion\nas a very visual thing."},{"time":5889,"text":"If I walk across this stage\nor gesture with my hands while I speak,"},{"time":10977,"text":"that motion is something that you can see."},{"time":14255,"text":"But there's a world of important motion\nthat's too subtle for the human eye,"},{"time":19737,"text":"and over the past few years,"},{"time":21778,"text":"we've started to find that cameras"},{"time":23775,"text":"can often see this motion\neven when humans can't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28305,"text":"So let me show you what I mean."},{"time":30717,"text":"On the left here, you see video\nof a person's wrist,"},{"time":34339,"text":"and on the right, you see video\nof a sleeping infant,"},{"time":37486,"text":"but if I didn't tell you\nthat these were videos,"},{"time":40632,"text":"you might assume that you were looking\nat two regular images,"},{"time":44393,"text":"because in both cases,"},{"time":46065,"text":"these videos appear to be\nalmost completely still."},{"time":50175,"text":"But there's actually a lot\nof subtle motion going on here,"},{"time":54060,"text":"and if you were to touch\nthe wrist on the left,"},{"time":56452,"text":"you would feel a pulse,"},{"time":58448,"text":"and if you were to hold\nthe infant on the right,"},{"time":60933,"text":"you would feel the rise\nand fall of her chest"},{"time":63324,"text":"as she took each breath."},{"time":65762,"text":"And these motions carry\na lot of significance,"},{"time":69338,"text":"but they're usually\ntoo subtle for us to see,"},{"time":72681,"text":"so instead, we have to observe them"},{"time":74957,"text":"through direct contact, through touch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78997,"text":"But a few years ago,"},{"time":80262,"text":"my colleagues at MIT developed\nwhat they call a motion microscope,"},{"time":84667,"text":"which is software that finds\nthese subtle motions in video"},{"time":89051,"text":"and amplifies them so that they\nbecome large enough for us to see."},{"time":93416,"text":"And so, if we use their software\non the left video,"},{"time":96899,"text":"it lets us see the pulse in this wrist,"},{"time":100149,"text":"and if we were to count that pulse,"},{"time":101844,"text":"we could even figure out\nthis person's heart rate."},{"time":105095,"text":"And if we used the same software\non the right video,"},{"time":108160,"text":"it lets us see each breath\nthat this infant takes,"},{"time":111387,"text":"and we can use this as a contact-free way\nto monitor her breathing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116884,"text":"And so this technology is really powerful\nbecause it takes these phenomena"},{"time":122232,"text":"that we normally have\nto experience through touch"},{"time":124599,"text":"and it lets us capture them visually\nand non-invasively."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129104,"text":"So a couple years ago, I started working\nwith the folks that created that software,"},{"time":133515,"text":"and we decided to pursue a crazy idea."},{"time":136882,"text":"We thought, it's cool\nthat we can use software"},{"time":139575,"text":"to visualize tiny motions like this,"},{"time":142710,"text":"and you can almost think of it\nas a way to extend our sense of touch."},{"time":147168,"text":"But what if we could do the same thing\nwith our ability to hear?"},{"time":152508,"text":"What if we could use video\nto capture the vibrations of sound,"},{"time":157173,"text":"which are just another kind of motion,"},{"time":160000,"text":"and turn everything that we see\ninto a microphone?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":164236,"text":"Now, this is a bit of a strange idea,"},{"time":166207,"text":"so let me try to put it\nin perspective for you."},{"time":169523,"text":"Traditional microphones\nwork by converting the motion"},{"time":173011,"text":"of an internal diaphragm\ninto an electrical signal,"},{"time":176610,"text":"and that diaphragm is designed\nto move readily with sound"},{"time":180928,"text":"so that its motion can be recorded\nand interpreted as audio."},{"time":185735,"text":"But sound causes all objects to vibrate."},{"time":189403,"text":"Those vibrations are just usually\ntoo subtle and too fast for us to see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194883,"text":"So what if we record them\nwith a high-speed camera"},{"time":198621,"text":"and then use software\nto extract tiny motions"},{"time":202197,"text":"from our high-speed video,"},{"time":204287,"text":"and analyze those motions to figure out\nwhat sounds created them?"},{"time":209859,"text":"This would let us turn visible objects\ninto visual microphones from a distance."},{"time":217080,"text":"And so we tried this out,"},{"time":219263,"text":"and here's one of our experiments,"},{"time":221190,"text":"where we took this potted plant\nthat you see on the right"},{"time":224139,"text":"and we filmed it with a high-speed camera"},{"time":226577,"text":"while a nearby loudspeaker\nplayed this sound."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230275,"text":"(Music: \"Mary Had a Little Lamb\")"}]},{"cues":[{"time":239820,"text":"And so here's the video that we recorded,"},{"time":242644,"text":"and we recorded it at thousands\nof frames per second,"},{"time":246568,"text":"but even if you look very closely,"},{"time":248890,"text":"all you'll see are some leaves"},{"time":250841,"text":"that are pretty much\njust sitting there doing nothing,"},{"time":253906,"text":"because our sound only moved those leaves\nby about a micrometer."},{"time":259103,"text":"That's one ten-thousandth of a centimeter,"},{"time":263379,"text":"which spans somewhere between\na hundredth and a thousandth"},{"time":267535,"text":"of a pixel in this image."},{"time":269881,"text":"So you can squint all you want,"},{"time":272768,"text":"but motion that small is pretty much\nperceptually invisible."},{"time":277667,"text":"But it turns out that something\ncan be perceptually invisible"},{"time":281824,"text":"and still be numerically significant,"},{"time":284633,"text":"because with the right algorithms,"},{"time":286635,"text":"we can take this silent,\nseemingly still video"},{"time":290322,"text":"and we can recover this sound."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292690,"text":"(Music: \"Mary Had a Little Lamb\")"}]},{"cues":[{"time":300074,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":310058,"text":"So how is this possible?"},{"time":311997,"text":"How can we get so much information\nout of so little motion?"},{"time":316341,"text":"Well, let's say that those leaves\nmove by just a single micrometer,"},{"time":321702,"text":"and let's say that that shifts our image\nby just a thousandth of a pixel."},{"time":327269,"text":"That may not seem like much,"},{"time":329841,"text":"but a single frame of video"},{"time":331837,"text":"may have hundreds of thousands\nof pixels in it,"},{"time":335094,"text":"and so if we combine all\nof the tiny motions that we see"},{"time":338548,"text":"from across that entire image,"},{"time":340846,"text":"then suddenly a thousandth of a pixel"},{"time":343469,"text":"can start to add up\nto something pretty significant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":346870,"text":"On a personal note, we were pretty psyched\nwhen we figured this out."},{"time":350505,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":352825,"text":"But even with the right algorithm,"},{"time":356078,"text":"we were still missing\na pretty important piece of the puzzle."},{"time":359695,"text":"You see, there are a lot of factors\nthat affect when and how well"},{"time":363299,"text":"this technique will work."},{"time":365296,"text":"There's the object and how far away it is;"},{"time":368500,"text":"there's the camera\nand the lens that you use;"},{"time":370894,"text":"how much light is shining on the object\nand how loud your sound is."},{"time":375945,"text":"And even with the right algorithm,"},{"time":379320,"text":"we had to be very careful\nwith our early experiments,"},{"time":382710,"text":"because if we got\nany of these factors wrong,"},{"time":385102,"text":"there was no way to tell\nwhat the problem was."},{"time":387470,"text":"We would just get noise back."},{"time":390117,"text":"And so a lot of our early\nexperiments looked like this."},{"time":393437,"text":"And so here I am,"},{"time":395643,"text":"and on the bottom left, you can kind of\nsee our high-speed camera,"},{"time":399683,"text":"which is pointed at a bag of chips,"},{"time":401866,"text":"and the whole thing is lit\nby these bright lamps."},{"time":404815,"text":"And like I said, we had to be\nvery careful in these early experiments,"},{"time":409180,"text":"so this is how it went down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411688,"text":"(Video) Abe Davis: Three, two, one, go."},{"time":415449,"text":"Mary had a little lamb!\nLittle lamb! Little lamb!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":420836,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":425336,"text":"AD: So this experiment\nlooks completely ridiculous."},{"time":428150,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":429938,"text":"I mean, I'm screaming at a bag of chips --"},{"time":432283,"text":"(Laughter) --"},{"time":433834,"text":"and we're blasting it with so much light,"},{"time":435951,"text":"we literally melted the first bag\nwe tried this on. (Laughter)"},{"time":440525,"text":"But ridiculous as this experiment looks,"},{"time":443799,"text":"it was actually really important,"},{"time":445587,"text":"because we were able\nto recover this sound."}]},{"cues":[{"time":448513,"text":"(Audio) Mary had a little lamb!\nLittle lamb! Little lamb!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":453225,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":457313,"text":"AD: And this was really significant,"},{"time":459194,"text":"because it was the first time\nwe recovered intelligible human speech"},{"time":463424,"text":"from silent video of an object."},{"time":465765,"text":"And so it gave us this point of reference,"},{"time":468156,"text":"and gradually we could start\nto modify the experiment,"},{"time":472106,"text":"using different objects\nor moving the object further away,"},{"time":475911,"text":"using less light or quieter sounds."},{"time":479887,"text":"And we analyzed all of these experiments"},{"time":482761,"text":"until we really understood\nthe limits of our technique,"},{"time":486383,"text":"because once we understood those limits,"},{"time":488333,"text":"we could figure out how to push them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":490679,"text":"And that led to experiments like this one,"},{"time":493860,"text":"where again, I'm going to speak\nto a bag of chips,"},{"time":496599,"text":"but this time we've moved our camera\nabout 15 feet away,"},{"time":501429,"text":"outside, behind a soundproof window,"},{"time":504262,"text":"and the whole thing is lit\nby only natural sunlight."},{"time":508529,"text":"And so here's the video that we captured."},{"time":512450,"text":"And this is what things sounded like\nfrom inside, next to the bag of chips."}]},{"cues":[{"time":517009,"text":"(Audio) Mary had a little lamb\nwhose fleece was white as snow,"},{"time":522047,"text":"and everywhere that Mary went,\nthat lamb was sure to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":527666,"text":"AD: And here's what we were able\nto recover from our silent video"},{"time":531683,"text":"captured outside behind that window."}]},{"cues":[{"time":534028,"text":"(Audio) Mary had a little lamb\nwhose fleece was white as snow,"},{"time":538463,"text":"and everywhere that Mary went,\nthat lamb was sure to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":543920,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":550421,"text":"AD: And there are other ways\nthat we can push these limits as well."},{"time":553963,"text":"So here's a quieter experiment"},{"time":555761,"text":"where we filmed some earphones\nplugged into a laptop computer,"},{"time":559871,"text":"and in this case, our goal was to recover\nthe music that was playing on that laptop"},{"time":563981,"text":"from just silent video"},{"time":566280,"text":"of these two little plastic earphones,"},{"time":568787,"text":"and we were able to do this so well"},{"time":570970,"text":"that I could even Shazam our results."},{"time":573431,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":577191,"text":"(Music: \"Under Pressure\" by Queen)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":589615,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":594584,"text":"And we can also push things\nby changing the hardware that we use."},{"time":599135,"text":"Because the experiments\nI've shown you so far"},{"time":601596,"text":"were done with a camera,\na high-speed camera,"},{"time":603918,"text":"that can record video\nabout a 100 times faster"},{"time":606797,"text":"than most cell phones,"},{"time":608724,"text":"but we've also found a way\nto use this technique"},{"time":611533,"text":"with more regular cameras,"},{"time":613763,"text":"and we do that by taking advantage\nof what's called a rolling shutter."},{"time":617832,"text":"You see, most cameras\nrecord images one row at a time,"},{"time":622630,"text":"and so if an object moves\nduring the recording of a single image,"},{"time":628344,"text":"there's a slight time delay\nbetween each row,"},{"time":631061,"text":"and this causes slight artifacts"},{"time":634218,"text":"that get coded into each frame of a video."},{"time":637701,"text":"And so what we found\nis that by analyzing these artifacts,"},{"time":641507,"text":"we can actually recover sound\nusing a modified version of our algorithm."},{"time":646122,"text":"So here's an experiment we did"},{"time":648034,"text":"where we filmed a bag of candy"},{"time":649729,"text":"while a nearby loudspeaker played"},{"time":651470,"text":"the same \"Mary Had a Little Lamb\"\nmusic from before,"},{"time":654442,"text":"but this time, we used just a regular\nstore-bought camera,"},{"time":658645,"text":"and so in a second, I'll play for you\nthe sound that we recovered,"},{"time":661819,"text":"and it's going to sound\ndistorted this time,"},{"time":663869,"text":"but listen and see if you can still\nrecognize the music."}]},{"cues":[{"time":667723,"text":"(Audio: \"Mary Had a Little Lamb\")"}]},{"cues":[{"time":685527,"text":"And so, again, that sounds distorted,"},{"time":688992,"text":"but what's really amazing here\nis that we were able to do this"},{"time":693378,"text":"with something\nthat you could literally run out"},{"time":696004,"text":"and pick up at a Best Buy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699122,"text":"So at this point,"},{"time":700485,"text":"a lot of people see this work,"},{"time":702459,"text":"and they immediately think\nabout surveillance."},{"time":705872,"text":"And to be fair,"},{"time":708287,"text":"it's not hard to imagine how you might use\nthis technology to spy on someone."},{"time":712420,"text":"But keep in mind that there's already\na lot of very mature technology"},{"time":716367,"text":"out there for surveillance."},{"time":717946,"text":"In fact, people have been using lasers"},{"time":720036,"text":"to eavesdrop on objects\nfrom a distance for decades."},{"time":723978,"text":"But what's really new here,"},{"time":726003,"text":"what's really different,"},{"time":727443,"text":"is that now we have a way\nto picture the vibrations of an object,"},{"time":731738,"text":"which gives us a new lens\nthrough which to look at the world,"},{"time":735151,"text":"and we can use that lens"},{"time":736661,"text":"to learn not just about forces like sound\nthat cause an object to vibrate,"},{"time":741560,"text":"but also about the object itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":744975,"text":"And so I want to take a step back"},{"time":746668,"text":"and think about how that might change\nthe ways that we use video,"},{"time":750917,"text":"because we usually use video\nto look at things,"},{"time":754470,"text":"and I've just shown you how we can use it"},{"time":756792,"text":"to listen to things."},{"time":758649,"text":"But there's another important way\nthat we learn about the world:"},{"time":762620,"text":"that's by interacting with it."},{"time":764895,"text":"We push and pull and poke and prod things."},{"time":768006,"text":"We shake things and see what happens."},{"time":771187,"text":"And that's something that video\nstill won't let us do,"},{"time":775460,"text":"at least not traditionally."},{"time":777596,"text":"So I want to show you some new work,"},{"time":779546,"text":"and this is based on an idea I had\njust a few months ago,"},{"time":782213,"text":"so this is actually the first time\nI've shown it to a public audience."},{"time":785514,"text":"And the basic idea is that we're going\nto use the vibrations in a video"},{"time":790877,"text":"to capture objects in a way\nthat will let us interact with them"},{"time":795358,"text":"and see how they react to us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":799120,"text":"So here's an object,"},{"time":800884,"text":"and in this case, it's a wire figure\nin the shape of a human,"},{"time":804716,"text":"and we're going to film that object\nwith just a regular camera."},{"time":807804,"text":"So there's nothing special\nabout this camera."},{"time":809928,"text":"In fact, I've actually done this\nwith my cell phone before."},{"time":812889,"text":"But we do want to see the object vibrate,"},{"time":815141,"text":"so to make that happen,"},{"time":816274,"text":"we're just going to bang a little bit\non the surface where it's resting"},{"time":819620,"text":"while we record this video."}]},{"cues":[{"time":827398,"text":"So that's it: just five seconds\nof regular video,"},{"time":831069,"text":"while we bang on this surface,"},{"time":833205,"text":"and we're going to use\nthe vibrations in that video"},{"time":836718,"text":"to learn about the structural\nand material properties of our object,"},{"time":841262,"text":"and we're going to use that information\nto create something new and interactive."},{"time":852866,"text":"And so here's what we've created."},{"time":855519,"text":"And it looks like a regular image,"},{"time":857748,"text":"but this isn't an image,\nand it's not a video,"},{"time":860859,"text":"because now I can take my mouse"},{"time":863227,"text":"and I can start interacting\nwith the object."},{"time":872936,"text":"And so what you see here"},{"time":875389,"text":"is a simulation of how this object"},{"time":877615,"text":"would respond to new forces\nthat we've never seen before,"},{"time":882073,"text":"and we created it from just\nfive seconds of regular video."}]},{"cues":[{"time":887249,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":897421,"text":"And so this is a really powerful\nway to look at the world,"},{"time":900648,"text":"because it lets us predict\nhow objects will respond"},{"time":903620,"text":"to new situations,"},{"time":905443,"text":"and you could imagine, for instance,\nlooking at an old bridge"},{"time":908916,"text":"and wondering what would happen,\nhow would that bridge hold up"},{"time":912443,"text":"if I were to drive my car across it."},{"time":915276,"text":"And that's a question\nthat you probably want to answer"},{"time":918050,"text":"before you start driving\nacross that bridge."},{"time":921988,"text":"And of course, there are going to be\nlimitations to this technique,"},{"time":925260,"text":"just like there were\nwith the visual microphone,"},{"time":927722,"text":"but we found that it works\nin a lot of situations"},{"time":930903,"text":"that you might not expect,"},{"time":932778,"text":"especially if you give it longer videos."}]},{"cues":[{"time":935546,"text":"So for example,\nhere's a video that I captured"},{"time":938054,"text":"of a bush outside of my apartment,"},{"time":940353,"text":"and I didn't do anything to this bush,"},{"time":943441,"text":"but by capturing a minute-long video,"},{"time":946146,"text":"a gentle breeze caused enough vibrations"},{"time":949524,"text":"that we could learn enough about this bush\nto create this simulation."},{"time":955270,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":961412,"text":"And so you could imagine giving this\nto a film director,"},{"time":964384,"text":"and letting him control, say,"},{"time":966103,"text":"the strength and direction of wind\nin a shot after it's been recorded."},{"time":972810,"text":"Or, in this case, we pointed our camera\nat a hanging curtain,"},{"time":977345,"text":"and you can't even see\nany motion in this video,"},{"time":981474,"text":"but by recording a two-minute-long video,"},{"time":984399,"text":"natural air currents in this room"},{"time":986837,"text":"created enough subtle,\nimperceptible motions and vibrations"},{"time":991249,"text":"that we could learn enough\nto create this simulation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":996243,"text":"And ironically,"},{"time":998609,"text":"we're kind of used to having\nthis kind of interactivity"},{"time":1001697,"text":"when it comes to virtual objects,"},{"time":1004344,"text":"when it comes to video games\nand 3D models,"},{"time":1007641,"text":"but to be able to capture this information\nfrom real objects in the real world"},{"time":1012045,"text":"using just simple, regular video,"},{"time":1014862,"text":"is something new that has\na lot of potential."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1018410,"text":"So here are the amazing people\nwho worked with me on these projects."},{"time":1024057,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1032819,"text":"And what I've shown you today\nis only the beginning."},{"time":1035876,"text":"We've just started to scratch the surface"},{"time":1037989,"text":"of what you can do\nwith this kind of imaging,"},{"time":1040961,"text":"because it gives us a new way"},{"time":1043342,"text":"to capture our surroundings\nwith common, accessible technology."},{"time":1048066,"text":"And so looking to the future,"},{"time":1049995,"text":"it's going to be\nreally exciting to explore"},{"time":1052032,"text":"what this can tell us about the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1054381,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1055610,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}